<section class="card">
  <h2>Show what you have done</h2>
  <p>
    Students can attach a screenshot, short note, photo of workbook pages, or a file export
    to show progress on homework and study.
  </p>

  <ul class="tight-list">
    <li>Screenshot of completed online work</li>
    <li>Photo of written homework</li>
    <li>Short reflection note</li>
    <li>Linked task completion</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="grid">
  <article class="card">
    <h3>Why evidence matters</h3>
    <p>
      Evidence helps students track progress, reflect on consistency, and show what they have done
      over time instead of relying on memory.
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="card">
    <h3>Useful evidence examples</h3>
    <ul class="tight-list">
      <li>Photo of maths workbook page</li>
      <li>Screenshot of typed English paragraph</li>
      <li>Short note on what was completed</li>
      <li>Reflection on what needs finishing next</li>
    </ul>
  </article>

  <article class="card">
    <h3>Next build step</h3>
    <p>
      This page can later link evidence directly to a task so students can prove completion against each homework item.
    </p>
  </article>
</section>